    "description": "Are you a skilled Property Consultant looking for your next big career move? Embassy Office Parks REIT in Bengaluru offers you the perfect platform to grow professionally and personally.\n\nAbout Embassy Office Parks REIT:\nEmbassy Office Parks REIT is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Provide advisory services on property investment and market trends\n• Manage relationships with existing customers post-purchase\n• Liaise with banks and NBFCs for home loan assistance to customers\n• Maintain a pipeline of qualified leads using CRM software\n• Achieve monthly and quarterly sales targets\n• Negotiate pricing, terms, and conditions on behalf of clients\n• Conduct site visits and property presentations for clients\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Master's degree preferred\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in RERA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Real Estate Law\n• Proficiency in Portfolio Management\n• Proficiency in GIS Tools\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in Title Search\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Flexible working hours\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Bengaluru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Embassy Office Parks REIT!",
